This paper deals with the computational complexity of computing an approximation of a trembling hand perfect equilibrium for a multi-player game in strategic form. This topic falls under the area of game theory, which is typically categorized under cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) in arXiv. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the complexity of the problem, which could also fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of approximation algorithms, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
